---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Features — SolanaForensics" description="Solana blockchain analysis modules via Telegram. Wallet tracing, token flow analysis, custodial audits, CEX cashout mapping, and LE-ready reports.">

  <div style="height: 70px;"></div>

  <section class="page-hero grid-bg">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tag">// Agent Modules</div>
      <h1>Forensic tools delivered via <span class="accent">Telegram.</span></h1>
      <p class="page-hero-sub">Five investigation modules accessible through @solanaforensics_bot. Ask a question, get forensic intelligence.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">

      <div class="feature-block" id="wallet-investigation">
        <div class="fb-header">
          <span class="fb-num mono">// 01</span>
          <h2>Wallet Investigation</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="fb-body">
          <div class="fb-desc">
            <p>Send a wallet address to the bot and receive a complete ecosystem map: hot wallets, staging addresses, intermediaries, and CEX endpoints. The bot resolves entities through Arkham, Solscan, and Helius, then analyses depositor outcomes to determine whether a wallet is connected to fraud.</p>
            <p>Multi-hop fund flow tracing follows assets regardless of how many intermediate wallets are used, exposing the full path from source to final destination.</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>Ecosystem mapping (hot wallets, staging, intermediaries, CEX endpoints)</li>
              <li>Entity resolution via Arkham, Solscan, Helius</li>
              <li>Depositor outcome analysis</li>
              <li>Multi-hop fund flow tracing</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="fb-visual">
            <div class="code-block mono">
<pre>WALLET REPORT: HdHZ...kQ3s
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Risk Score:     <span style="color:#ff3366">94/100 [CRITICAL]</span>
Entity:         Unknown — flagged cluster
Funding Source: Binance withdrawal (3 hops)
CEX Endpoints:  Kraken deposit (2 confirmed)
Depositors:     847 wallets identified
Outcome:        <span style="color:#ff3366">94% losses > 80%</span>
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
<span style="color:#00ff88">Recommended: Freeze request — Kraken EU</span></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-block" id="token-tracing">
        <div class="fb-header">
          <span class="fb-num mono">// 02</span>
          <h2>Token Tracing</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="fb-body">
          <div class="fb-desc">
            <p>Track the movement of any SPL token — USDC, USDT, or custom mints — across the Solana network. The bot analyses token mint and burn activity to identify manipulation, and maps cross-token movement patterns where SOL converts to stablecoins before hitting a CEX.</p>
            <p>Circular flow detection identifies wash trading patterns designed to create the illusion of legitimate volume or obscure the origin of funds.</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>SPL token flow analysis (USDC, USDT, any SPL token)</li>
              <li>Token mint/burn activity tracking</li>
              <li>Cross-token movement (SOL → stables → CEX)</li>
              <li>Wash trading &amp; circular flow detection</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-block" id="custodial-audits">
        <div class="fb-header">
          <span class="fb-num mono">// 03</span>
          <h2>Custodial Platform Audits</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="fb-body">
          <div class="fb-desc">
            <p>Submit a custodial platform's wallet infrastructure and the bot runs a 6-point fraud checklist: yield mathematics viability, depositor outcome analysis, insider extraction patterns, on-chain solvency verification, CEX cashout mapping, and predecessor operation detection.</p>
            <p>The bot also analyses DeFi protocol interactions — Orca, Jupiter, Raydium — to separate legitimate activity from facade operations designed to create the appearance of trading.</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>6-point fraud checklist: yield math, depositor outcomes, insider extraction, solvency, CEX cashouts, predecessor ops</li>
              <li>DeFi protocol interaction analysis (Orca, Jupiter, Raydium)</li>
              <li>Legitimate activity vs facade separation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-block" id="cex-cashout">
        <div class="fb-header">
          <span class="fb-num mono">// 04</span>
          <h2>CEX Cashout Mapping</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="fb-body">
          <div class="fb-desc">
            <p>Identify exchange deposit addresses across 10+ major centralised exchanges. The bot maps the intermediary chain from suspect wallets to known exchange deposit addresses, documenting every hop for evidence packaging.</p>
            <p>Output includes structured evidence packages ready for freeze and seizure requests to exchange compliance departments, with full transaction citations and intermediary documentation.</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>Exchange deposit address identification across 10+ major CEXs</li>
              <li>Binance, Kraken, OKX, Bybit, Coinbase, KuCoin, Gate.io, HTX, MEXC, Bitget</li>
              <li>Evidence packaging for freeze/seizure requests</li>
              <li>Intermediary chain documentation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="feature-block" id="le-reports">
        <div class="fb-header">
          <span class="fb-num mono">// 05</span>
          <h2>Law Enforcement Reports</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="fb-body">
          <div class="fb-desc">
            <p>Generate PDF forensic reports formatted for police submissions and court proceedings. Each report includes on-chain evidence citations, complete timeline reconstruction, and recommended enforcement actions including which jurisdictions and exchanges to target.</p>
            <p>Reports are designed to be attached directly to criminal complaints, SAR filings, or civil asset recovery proceedings without additional formatting.</p>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li>PDF forensic reports — police-ready, court-ready</li>
              <li>On-chain evidence citations</li>
              <li>Timeline reconstruction</li>
              <li>Recommended actions (freeze requests, blacklist addresses, jurisdictions)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section" style="background: var(--bg-2); border-top: 1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <div class="tag">// Start Investigating</div>
      <h2>Try SolanaForensics on Telegram.</h2>
      <p>Open @solanaforensics_bot and send a wallet address to get started.</p>
      <a href="https://t.me/solanaforensics_bot" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary">Start on Telegram →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.page-hero {
  padding: 6rem 0 5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.page-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 4vw, 4rem); max-width: 700px; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
.page-hero-sub { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 1.05rem; max-width: 540px; line-height: 1.7; }

.feature-block {
  padding: 4rem 0;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
}
.feature-block:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

.fb-header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
}

.fb-num {
  font-size: 0.8rem;
  color: var(--accent);
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
}

.fb-header h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2.25rem); }

.fb-body {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: start;
}

.fb-body:not(:has(.fb-visual)) {
  grid-template-columns: 1fr;
  max-width: 680px;
}

.fb-desc p {
  color: var(--text-muted);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
}

.feature-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.625rem;
}

.feature-list li {
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  padding-left: 1.25rem;
  position: relative;
}

.feature-list li::before {
  content: '→';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--accent);
  font-size: 0.8rem;
}

.code-block {
  background: #060b14;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-glow);
  padding: 1.5rem;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--success);
  overflow-x: auto;
}

.code-block pre { margin: 0; }

.cta-inner {
  text-align: center;
  padding: 6rem 0;
}
.cta-inner h2 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
.cta-inner p { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .page-hero { padding: 4rem 0 3rem; }
  .page-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 5vw, 3rem); }
  .page-hero-sub { font-size: 0.95rem; }

  .fb-body { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
  .feature-block { padding: 3rem 0; }
  .fb-header { gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }
  .fb-header h2 { font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3.5vw, 1.75rem); }

  .code-block { padding: 1rem; font-size: 0.72rem; }
  .code-block pre { white-space: pre-wrap; word-break: break-all; }

  .feature-list li { font-size: 0.82rem; }

  .cta-inner { padding: 4rem 0; }
  .cta-inner h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.25rem); }
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .page-hero { padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
  .feature-block { padding: 2rem 0; }
  .fb-header { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: flex-start; }
  .fb-desc p { font-size: 0.88rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .code-block { padding: 0.875rem; font-size: 0.65rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .cta-inner { padding: 3rem 0; }
}
</style>
